# TFS_RUST — Cursor rules

`AGENTS.md` and these `.mdc` files are the binding project rules. If any are missing from context, add them with `@` (e.g. `@.cursor/rules/TFS-Core.mdc`).

## Always apply (`alwaysApply: true` in each file)

- `.cursor/rules/TFS-Core.mdc` — role, stack, 1:1 parity with TFS 1.4.2 C++
- `.cursor/rules/TFS-Workflow.mdc`
- `.cursor/rules/TFS-cpp-references.mdc`
- `.cursor/rules/TFS-entity-storage.mdc`
- `.cursor/rules/TFS-rust-idioms.mdc`
- `.cursor/rules/TFS-threading.mdc`
- `.cursor/rules/tfs-output-format.mdc` — response/output format; `globs: ["**/*"]`

## Apply when working in these areas (path `globs` in each file; `@` them for other work)

- `.cursor/rules/TFS-packets.mdc` — `crates/tfs-rust-net/**/*.rs`
- `.cursor/rules/TFS-database.mdc` — `crates/tfs-rust-db/**/*.rs`
- `.cursor/rules/TFS-lua-boundaries.mdc` — `crates/tfs-rust-core/**/*.rs`, `crates/tfs-rust-lua/**/*.rs`
